# My Current Reading List

Curious about what to read next? Here’s a peek into what I am currently reading.  

  ___

**Pet Sematary** by Stephen King  

- This horror classic by Stephen King exploring death and the supernatural. This is my first foray into Stephen King, I love the simplicity of the writing and character development.  

   [Amazon](https://amzn.to/3BHO15L) | [Wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pet_Sematary)  

**Michael Jordan: The Life** by Roland Lazenby  

- A comprehensive biography on the basketball GOAT. Having enjoyed *The Last Dance* on Netflix, I'm excited to explore Jordan’s world further.  

   [Amazon](https://amzn.to/4f3VtXd) | [Wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roland_Lazenby)  

**Slouching Towards Bethlehem** by Joan Didion  

- A collection of essays about the culture and counterculture of 1960s America. So many great writers admire Didion, I’m starting my journey with this book.  

   [Amazon](https://amzn.to/3BLDRRL) | [Wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slouching_Towards_Bethlehem)  

**The 48 Laws of Power** by Robert Greene  

- A monster guide to understanding power dynamics, leadership, strategy, and influence. I’m in no great rush to finish this book and have been slowly chipping away at it one law at a time.  

   [Amazon](https://amzn.to/3AaVcmt) | [Wiki](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_48_Laws_of_Power)  

___

